******What is Abstraction?
Definition
Abstraction means hiding the implementation details and showing only the essential functionality to the user.

Simple Definition
Show WHAT to do, hide HOW it is done.

What does Abstraction mean?
Break the word:
Abstraction
↓
Hide unnecessary details
↓
Show only important features
Why Do We Need Abstraction?

Suppose you drive a car.

You only know:

Start Car

Brake

Accelerator

Steering

Do you know how the engine, gearbox, fuel injection, and pistons work?

❌ No.

You don't need to know.
The car hides all internal implementation.
This is Abstraction.


**Abstraction in Programming
Suppose you are creating an Animal class.

Every animal makes a sound.

But Animal doesn't know what sound to make.

So we write
abstract class Animal {
    abstract void sound();
}

Notice:

We only say
Every animal must have sound()
We don't say how.

Child Classes

Dog

class Dog extends Animal {

    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Bark");
    }
}

Cat

class Cat extends Animal {

    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Meow");
    }
}

Now

Animal a = new Dog();

a.sound();

Output

Bark
