How is Abstraction Achieved?

There are 2 ways:

Abstraction

↓

1. Abstract Class

2. Interface
1. Abstract Class

An abstract class is a class that

Cannot create objects
May contain abstract methods
May contain normal methods

Example

abstract class Animal {

    abstract void sound();

    void sleep() {
        System.out.println("Sleeping");
    }
}

Here

sound()

↓

Abstract Method

sleep()

↓

Normal Method
Abstract Method

An abstract method has

No body
Only declaration
abstract void sound();

Wrong

abstract void sound(){

}

Compile Error.

Why?

Because

Parent doesn't know implementation.

Child will implement it.

Child Class
class Dog extends Animal {

    @Override
    void sound() {

        System.out.println("Bark");

    }

}
Object Creation

Can we create

Animal a = new Animal();

❌ No.

Because Animal is abstract.

Correct

Animal a = new Dog();
Why?

Dog provides the implementation of

sound()
